The article reports that President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has issued an Executive Order declaring a national emergency to address the threat posed by the advancement of sensitive technologies and products by certain countries. The order aims to protect the military, intelligence, surveillance, and cyber capabilities of the United States. It states that countries of concern have comprehensive strategies to advance these technologies, including acquiring cutting-edge technologies from around the world. China, along with the Special Administrative Regions of Hong Kong and Macau, is identified as a country of concern. The order directs the Secretary of the Treasury to issue regulations requiring US persons to provide information on certain transactions involving foreign persons and prohibits certain other transactions. The letter from President Biden includes a copy of the Executive Order.